---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---
<BaseLayout title="How I Work" description="My process for building, hardening, and delivering high‑integrity software.">
  <div class="hand-drawn-frame p-8">
    <h1 class="hand-drawn-heading text-3xl mb-6">How I Work</h1>
    <p class="mb-6 text-gray-mid">I build real systems where correctness matters. My process is transparent, iterative, and heavily automated.</p>
    <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-3 text-gray-mid">
      <li><strong>Patch plans</strong> – define scope, acceptance criteria, and regression checklists before any code change.</li>
      <li><strong>Incremental development</strong> – small, test‑covered commits pushed to CI.</li>
      <li><strong>Automated QA</strong> – unit, integration, and performance tests run on every PR.</li>
      <li><strong>AI‑assisted workflow</strong> – I use Claude, Codex, and Copilot for code generation, review, and documentation, but every suggestion is vetted by a human.</li>
      <li><strong>Hardening focus</strong> – data‑integrity layers, staleness gates, and time‑normalization are baked into every project.</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>